article.description: Jamel Waters scored 16 points with five rebounds as Alabama State edged Alabama A&M 74-68 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Alabama State edges Alabama A&M 74-68
article.story: NORMAL, Ala. -- Jamel Waters scored 16 points with five rebounds as Alabama State edged Alabama A&M 74-68 on Saturday night. Glenn Hollaway added 12 points and nine rebounds for the Hornets (9-15, 4-8 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Terrance LeFlore and Bobby Brown had 10 points apiece. The team hit 43 percent from the field overall -- including 8 of 19 from distance -- and 62.5 percent from the line. The Bulldogs (8-13, 4-8) had a 33-31 edge at the break but Alabama State overtook them in the second half, outscoring them 43-35. Alabama A&M was 50 percent from the field overall -- including just 1 of 14 from distance -- and 74 percent from the line. Nicholas West and Quinterian McConico scored 18 points apiece for the Bulldogs. West also led the team with 10 rebounds.
